The White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest, gave a press briefing on October 17, 2014. He discussed various topics including the response to the Ebola outbreak, the appointment of Ron Klain as the Ebola Response Coordinator, and the international response to the outbreak. Earnest emphasized the administration's focus on protecting the American public and the need for coordination and implementation in the response efforts. He also addressed concerns about health workers traveling and the level of fear among the public. Earnest mentioned that the President has been making calls to world leaders to enlist their support and resources in the response to the outbreak. He concluded the briefing by providing a brief overview of the President's schedule for the following week.